          "intro": "A few of the more common issues, and what tends to fix them.",
          "items": [
            {
              "symptom": "Pastry shrinks on baking",
              "cause": "Not rested before going in, or dough overworked.",
              "fix": "Chill the lined tin for 30 minutes before blind-baking. Handle pastry as little as possible."
            },
            {
              "symptom": "Filling sets but pastry stays soggy",
              "cause": "Filling went in before blind-baking, or eggs leaked through cracks.",
              "fix": "Blind-bake the pastry case first with baking beans for 15 minutes, then 5 minutes without to crisp the base. Brush with beaten egg to seal any cracks."
            },
            {
              "symptom": "Filling curdled or cracked",
              "cause": "Baked too hot.",
              "fix": "Drop the oven to 160°C. A custard filling should be set at the edges with a slight wobble in the middle when done."
            },
            {
              "symptom": "Top burnt before middle set",
              "cause": "Tin too deep, or oven too hot.",
              "fix": "Cover loosely with foil for the last 10 minutes if the top is going. Use a wider, shallower tin for deeper fillings."
            }
